spans.text: our hearts , unknowing where to rest
plenty , ease , and indolence of mind
plenty , ease , and indolence of mind
listless , weary , sick , chagrined at home , In search of happiness abroad
What a whole thankless land thy worth denies
You'll hardly match the pleasures she can give
a multitude succeeds — She wants an heir
a title , or she wants a gown
proves the man or poor , or much a slave
the man or poor , or much a slave
Then muzzle not the ox who treads the corn
Then muzzle not the ox who treads the corn
that thing on earth , a happy man
tell us , if you can , Is there that thing on earth , a happy man ?
Blessed in his fame , and in his fortune blessed , No craving void
to lay down his load of life
barren deserts , and untrodden ways : Thirsty and faint , his nerves new vigour strings , And full of thee he quaffs immortal springs
through thee walks worthy of his God
cloudless all appears , A short , but smiling train of happy years
all beyond the promised land of peace
